.TH SIMPLE-MCP 1 "November 2025" "0.6" "Simple MCP Manual"
.SH NAME
simple-mcp \- Simple Model Context Protocol (MCP) server in Go
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple-mcp
[\fI\-config file\fR] [\fI\-listen-addr address\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple-mcp
is a lightweight server implementing the Model Context Protocol (MCP). It is designed to bridge Large Language Model (LLM) agents with the local Linux system.

It exposes a set of "Tools" (executable commands) and "Resources" (static or dynamic system data) defined in a YAML configuration file. This allows an LLM to query system status (e.g., uptime, logs) or perform actions (e.g., upgrades, reboots) in a controlled environment.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-config " file"
Path to the YAML configuration file.
.br
Default: \fI./simple-mcp.yaml\fR (or \fI/etc/simple-mcp/simple-mcp.yaml\fR when running as a system service).
.TP
.BI \-listen-addr " address"
The network address and port to listen on for HTTP requests.
.br
Default: \fI:8080\fR
.SH CONFIGURATION
The behavior of the server is defined in \fBsimple-mcp.yaml\fR.
.P
This file defines:
.IP \[bu] 2
\fBContextItems (Tools):\fR Commands the LLM can execute. Supports synchronous and asynchronous execution (for long-running tasks).
.IP \[bu]
\fBResources:\fR Data endpoints the LLM can read (e.g., file contents or command output).
.P
Example configuration location: \fI/etc/simple-mcp/simple-mcp.yaml\fR
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/simple-mcp/simple-mcp.yaml
The default system-wide configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/simple-mcp.service
The systemd unit file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Run manually with a local config:
.P
.RS 4
simple-mcp -config ./my-config.yaml
.RE
.P
.B Run on a specific port:
.P
.RS 4
simple-mcp -listen-addr 127.0.0.1:9090
.RE
